  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6576.28 sitting just below the GEX flip at 6590, dealers are currently in positive gamma territory and likely **selling into this momentum** as spot approaches the heavy resistance cluster at 6575-6580 where over 7.4B in positive gamma creates a natural ceiling. The PIN regime suggests dealers will continue to fade this move higher, especially with spot now testing the max positive gamma strike at 6580 where mechanical selling pressure intensifies.\n\n**Watch for rejection at 6580** as dealers unload delta hedges, but any break above 6590 flips the script and could trigger accelerated buying toward 6600+ as dealers shift to negative gamma above the flip strike.",
